According to a new report from Intel Market Research, the global Color Prestained Protein Standard market was valued at USD 636 million in 2025 and is projected to reach USD 932 million by 2034, exhibiting a CAGR of 5.7% during the forecast period (2025–2034). This growth is driven by the accelerating pace of biomedical research, expanding proteomics pipelines, and the widespread adoption of automated electrophoresis platforms across academic, biopharma, and contract research environments.
A Color Prestained Protein Standard is a mixture of proteins with precisely known molecular weights that are pre‑labeled with colored dyes. Researchers use these standards in SDS‑PAGE and related electrophoretic techniques to estimate the molecular weight of unknown proteins, monitor gel migration in real‑time, and ensure consistent lane performance without the need for post‑run staining. By providing immediate visual cues, they enable faster decision‑making and improve reproducibility in downstream applications such as Western blotting, protein purification, and quantitative proteomics.
